class Solution {
public:
    long long minEnd(int n, int x) {
        --n;
        long long res = x;
        long long mask = 1;
        while (n) {
            if (!(x & mask)) {
                if (n & 1) res |= mask;
                n >>= 1;
            }
            mask <<= 1;
        }
        return res;
    }
};
```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(log(n) + log(x))
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: Treat the strictly increasing sequence as x OR k for k = 0,1,2,...,n-1 while ensuring the AND remains x by only setting bits that are 0 in x. The minimal last element is x OR (n-1) after skipping the bits already set in x.

